🔵 Azure AD API Permissions (for Azure App Account)
For inputs that use the Windows Azure Service Management API, select Access Azure Service Management as organization under Delegated Permissions in the app registration. ￼



|Permission                                     |Type     |Used By                                                                 |
|-----------------------------------------------|---------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`user_impersonation` (Azure Service Management)|Delegated|Azure Audit, Azure Resource, Azure Metrics, Azure Consumption, Azure KQL|

Note: Most permissions for this add-on are Azure RBAC roles (IAM), not Microsoft Graph API permissions — which is the key difference from the Splunk Add-on for Microsoft Office 365.

⚠️ Key Notes
	•	To collect data from Azure Audit and Azure Resources, you must configure a Microsoft Entra ID application with read permissions. ￼
	•	A Premium P1 license or higher is required to grant the app registration Reader access to your subscription. ￼
	•	For Event Hub inputs on Splunk Cloud, you must use the Admin Configuration Service (ACS) to configure outbound ports 5671/tcp and 5672/tcp (AMQP) to connect to the target Azure address. ￼
	•	Storage Table and Storage Blob inputs do not use Azure AD app credentials — they authenticate directly via a Storage Account connection string or key.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​